abstract: But does she have Trumps number? And what is going on with him anyway?
snippet: But does she have Trumps number? And what is going on with him anyway?
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Hi, Gail. Did you read our friend Frank Brunis column this past weekend? Its one of the most thought-provoking articles Ive read in a while about the likely shape of the 2020 race, and it contains this fascinating nugget: 19 Republicans in Congress have already announced that they wont seek another term in their current office, and most of them are just retiring from politics altogether instead of seeking a higher office.

abstract: The presidential hopefuls detailed their views on the limits of executive power in response to a New York Times survey.
snippet: The presidential hopefuls detailed their views on the limits of executive power in response to a New York Times survey.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON  Democratic presidential candidates broadly agree that President Trump has shaken the presidency loose from its constitutional limits and say that the White House needs major new legal curbs, foreshadowing a potential era of reform akin to the post-Watergate period if any of them wins next years election.
